# Prezence base rules

## Monorepo commands — always use pnpm + filter
```bash
pnpm dev --filter=api      # run NestJS only
pnpm dev --filter=web      # run Next.js only
pnpm dev                   # run everything
pnpm test --filter=api     # test NestJS only
pnpm lint                  # lint everything
pnpm build                 # build everything
```
Never use npm or yarn. Never run commands without --filter unless intentional.

## TypeScript
- Strict mode everywhere. Never use `any` type.
- Always type function return values explicitly.
- Use Zod for runtime validation at API boundaries.

## Git
- Never push directly to main.
- Always work on feature/xxx or fix/xxx branches.
- All PRs merge into develop, not main.
- Commit messages: "feat:", "fix:", "chore:", "refactor:", "test:"

## Hard rules
- Never call payment gateways directly — always PaymentService
- Never store OAuth tokens without AES-256-GCM encryption
- Never use console.log in source — use NestJS Logger
- Never commit .env files or hardcoded secrets
